The Joint Action Committee (JAC) of the Academic Staff Union of Universities(ASUU), Senior Staff Association of Nigerian Universities (SSANU) and the Non-Academic Staff Union of Universities (NASU) of the Lagos State University (LASU) chapter has cancelled the earlier planned strike action scheduled to hold on Monday, January 18, 2021. In a joint statement signed and dated 17th January, 2021 by the chairmen and secretaries of the respective unions and which has just been made available to Daily Independent via the office of LASU spokesman, Ademola Adekoya, the Joint Action Committee explained that, having been assuaged by the intervention and assurances of the Acting Vice-Chancellor, Prof. Oyedamola Oke, the unions have decided to revert their stand on the cesation of their services effective from January 18. This means that the semester examinations scheduled to begin on the same Monday, January 18, 2021 are expected to go on without any hinderance. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCEÂ DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM!